comments: Reaves (LAL) maintains his arms within the frame of his body and absorbs the incoming contact from Sengun (HOU) during the screen.
Brooks (HOU) contests James' (LAL) jump shot and the contact after the release, and follow-through, is marginal.
Sengun (HOU) establishes himself in Reddish's (LAL) path, firms up, and absorbs the incoming contact from Reddish (LAL) during the pick.

Reddish (LAL) establishes himself in Sengun's (HOU) path and slightly turns his body as he braces for the incoming contact, which is marginal and does not dislodge Sengun from his legally obtained position.
Davis (LAL) extends his arms in VanVleet's (HOU) path and collapses them during the pick, which is marginal.
Brooks (HOU) makes marginal contact with James' (LAL) body while defending the drive to the basket and shot attempt.
Davis (LAL) jumps alongside Sengun's (HOU) path and marginal body contact occurs during the driving shot attempt.
Sengun (HOU) establishes a legal guarding position outside of the RA and in Davis' (LAL) path as he absorbs the contact during the driving shot attempt.
Green (HOU) maintains his arms within the frame of his body and absorbs the incoming contact from Hachimura (LAL) during the screen.
Hachimura (LAL) briefly places his hand to Sengun's (HOU) off-arm and immediately removes it during the drive, which does not affect Sengun's SQBR.
James (LAL) is in the paint for less than three seconds when the shot is imminent.
Hachimura (LAL) contests the driving shot attempt and incidental "high-five" contact occurs with Sengun (HOU) after the release.
Brooks (HOU) contests Reaves's (LAL) jump shot and the contact after the release, and follow-through, is marginal.
Green (HOU) gives a step of distance when establishing himself in Hachimura's (LAL) path and marginal contact occurs during the screen.
Hachimura (LAL) maintains verticality and absorbs the contact that occurs during Sengun's (HOU) layup attempt.
Smith Jr. (HOU) reaches in and makes contact to Reaves' (LAL) body that affects his SQBR.

Brooks (HOU) makes incidental contact to Reaves' (LAL) head as he pursues the rebound. Contact to an opponent's head/face can be deemed marginal when the result of a natural basketball move, provided the contact is not disproportionate or uncontrolled.
Green (HOU) establishes himself in James's (LAL) path and absorbs the incoming contact during the screen.
James (LAL) briefly places his hand to Sengun's (HOU) front and extends his arm at the start of the drive, which does not affect Sengun's SQBR.
While contesting the post play and shot attempt, James (LAL) makes marginal contact with Sengun (HOU) while contesting the driving shot attempt.
Prior to James (LAL) receiving the incoming pass, he maintains a legal obtained position in front of Brooks (HOU) and does not dislodge him.
Brooks (HOU) briefly grasps James' (LAL) jersey at the start of the drive, which does not affect his SQBR.
Eason (HOU) lowers his arm and  initiates contact with James's (LAL) head, which affects his driving shot attempt.
James (LAL) legally contests Brooks's (HOU) jump shot, making "high-five" contact after the ball is released.
